<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  OWASP Dependency-Check suppressions.

  Add an entry per false positive or per accepted residual risk. Each
  entry MUST cite (a) the CVE id, (b) the package coordinate, (c) the
  reasoning. Without the third, the suppression is opaque and rots.

  Template:

  <suppress until="YYYY-MM-DD">
    <notes>Why this CVE doesn't apply / accepted residual risk.</notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/group/artifact@.*$</packageUrl>
    <cve>CVE-YYYY-NNNNN</cve>
  </suppress>

  Re-evaluate suppressions on every release. The `until` attribute makes
  expired suppressions show up as warnings.
-->
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">

  <!-- ===================================================================
       OWASP-SUPP-001: Quarkus 3.27.2 framework CVE (CVE-2026-39852, 8.2)
       — RESOLVED by the QUARKUS-3.37-PLATFORM-MIGRATION upgrade (#2382).
       =================================================================== -->
  <!--
    CVE-2026-39852 (Quarkus ARC CDI context-manipulation) was fixed upstream in
    the Quarkus 3.37.1 platform BOM. After the 3.27.2 → 3.37.1 migration the scan
    no longer associates this CVE with any io.quarkus jar, so the suppression is
    removed rather than re-targeted (re-targeting to @3.37.1 would only produce a
    zero-match rule). This is the intended outcome of the migration: the upgrade
    is the fix. If a future scan re-surfaces a Quarkus-3.37 CDI CVE, add a fresh
    entry then. OWASP-SUPP-001 retired 2026-07-07.
  -->

  <!-- ===================================================================
       OWASP-SUPP-002: Neo4j server CVEs — false positives via CPE mismatch
       ===================================================================
       CVE-2026-1524 (9.8), CVE-2026-1497 (7.2), CVE-2021-34371 (9.8)

       OWASP Dependency-Check assigns CPE cpe:2.3:a:neo4j:neo4j:X.Y to every
       artifact whose GAV version matches a Neo4j database server CVE target
       range. The three client-side Neo4j libraries below are NOT the server
       binary: neo4j-ogm-core is an ORM layer, neo4j-migrations is a schema
       migration runner, and neo4j-cypher-dsl is a query builder DSL. None
       exposes a Bolt server port or an RPC endpoint. All matches are false
       positives from CPE version-number coincidence.
       =================================================================== -->
