  <!-- ===================================================================
       OWASP-SUPP-003 / OWASP-SIBLING-JARS-6:
       Apache Jena 5.4.0 — ALL module JARs
       (CVE-2025-49656 CVSS 7.5, CVE-2025-50151 CVSS 8.8)
       =================================================================== -->
  <!--
    Genuine CVEs in Apache Jena 5.4.0. Jena is used for server-side SPARQL
    processing of internal RDF data. User-supplied SPARQL queries do NOT reach
    the Jena parser directly — all queries are constructed server-side from
    validated API parameters or loaded from trusted ontology files. No remote
    SPARQL endpoint is exposed to untrusted callers. Accepted residual risk
    pending availability of a patched Jena 5.x release; re-evaluate on next
    Jena version upgrade.

    Wildcard covers ALL org.apache.jena 5.4.0 module JARs (jena-core, jena-arq,
    jena-iri, jena-iri3986, jena-base, jena-shacl, jena-tdb2, jena-rdfconnection,
    and any other sibling modules pulled in by transitive dependencies). Uses the
    same wildcard pattern as OWASP-SUPP-004 (Netty) to avoid per-jar whack-a-mole.
    Consolidates OWASP-SUPP-003 + OWASP-SIBLING-JARS-2 through SIBLING-JARS-5.
    OWASP-SIBLING-JARS-6.
  -->
  <suppress until="2026-12-31">
    <notes>CVE-2025-49656 (CVSS 7.5): Apache Jena 5.4.0 CVE. Wildcard covers ALL
    org.apache.jena 5.4.0 module JARs. Jena processes internal RDF data only;
    no user-supplied SPARQL or IRI input reaches the Jena parser directly. All queries
    are server-constructed from validated parameters or trusted ontology files.
    Accepted residual risk pending patched Jena release. OWASP-SIBLING-JARS-6.</notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.apache\.jena/.*@5\.4\.0$</packageUrl>
    <cve>CVE-2025-49656</cve>
  </suppress>
  <suppress until="2026-12-31">
    <notes>CVE-2025-50151 (CVSS 8.8): Apache Jena 5.4.0 CVE. Same wildcard and reasoning
    as the CVE-2025-49656 entry above — no user-supplied SPARQL or IRI input; all
    server-constructed. OWASP-SIBLING-JARS-6.</notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.apache\.jena/.*@5\.4\.0$</packageUrl>
    <cve>CVE-2025-50151</cve>
  </suppress>

  <!-- ===================================================================
       OWASP-SUPP-004: Netty 4.1.135.Final (CVE-2026-42582, 7.5)
       (re-targeted from 4.1.133.Final; QUARKUS-3.37 shifted the version)
       =================================================================== -->
  <!--
    CVE-2026-42582 affects Netty's specialised protocol codecs (the PROXY-protocol
    decoder / HTTP-3 codec), matched by OWASP against the whole io.netty 4.1.135.Final
    stack via the broad netty:netty CPE. shepard imports no io.netty artifact directly
    — the version is dictated by the Quarkus 3.37.1 platform BOM and is not directly
    controllable without a stray override fighting the BOM. Structurally, shepard's
    Quarkus HTTP listener sits behind the Caddy reverse proxy (TLS termination), and
    enables neither the HAProxy PROXY-protocol decoder nor an HTTP/3 listener — the
    codepaths the CVE targets are not on any exposed path. Accepted residual risk;
    re-evaluate on the next Quarkus/Netty bump. OWASP-SUPP-004.
  -->
  <suppress until="2026-12-31">
    <notes>CVE-2026-42582 (CVSS 7.5): Netty 4.1.135.Final CVE (specialised PROXY/HTTP-3
    codecs). BOM-managed transitive via Quarkus 3.37.1; not directly controllable.
    External traffic terminates at the Caddy reverse proxy before reaching Netty, and
    shepard enables neither the HAProxy PROXY-protocol decoder nor an HTTP/3 listener.
    Accepted residual risk pending upstream Quarkus/Netty upgrade. OWASP-SUPP-004.</notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/io\.netty/.*@4\.1\.135\.Final$</packageUrl>
    <cve>CVE-2026-42582</cve>
  </suppress>

  <!-- ===================================================================
       OWASP-SUPP-005: Eclipse Angus angus-activation 2.0.3 (CVE-2025-7962, 7.5)
       — false positive / mis-attributed jar (re-targeted from 2.0.2)
       =================================================================== -->
  <!--
    CVE-2025-7962 is an SMTP CR/LF injection in the Angus Mail *SMTP provider*
    (org.eclipse.angus:smtp), fixed in 2.0.4. OWASP dependency-check mis-attributes
    it to the co-versioned Jakarta *Activation* implementation jar
    (org.eclipse.angus:angus-activation) — a distinct artifact that carries no SMTP
    code (tracked upstream as dependency-check issue #8144). Two independent reasons
    this is not exploitable here:
      (a) The actual vulnerable artifacts (org.eclipse.angus:jakarta.mail + :smtp)
          are already pinned to the fixed 2.0.5 via <dependencyManagement> in
          backend/pom.xml, so the real SMTP provider is patched.
      (b) angus-activation is the Jakarta Activation datatype/mailcap resolver; it
          contains no SMTP send path, so the CVE's codepath is absent from this jar.
    Re-targeted 2.0.2 → 2.0.3 (the version the fixed jakarta.mail 2.0.5 resolves the
    activation impl to). OWASP-SUPP-005.
  -->
  <suppress until="2026-12-31">
    <notes>CVE-2025-7962 (CVSS 7.5): False positive / mis-attribution. CVE targets the
    Angus SMTP provider org.eclipse.angus:smtp (fixed 2.0.4); dependency-check flags the
    co-versioned org.eclipse.angus:angus-activation 2.0.3 instead (a distinct Jakarta
    Activation jar with no SMTP code — dep-check issue #8144). The real smtp + jakarta.mail
    artifacts are pinned to the fixed 2.0.5 via dependencyManagement. OWASP-SUPP-005.</notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.eclipse\.angus/angus-activation@2\.0\.3$</packageUrl>
    <cve>CVE-2025-7962</cve>
  </suppress>

